§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ The ❬real sum❭ of two real numbers $R$ and $S$ is the set
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ \Set{t ∈ 𝗤}{∃r ∈ R, s ∈ S \text{ with } t = r + s}. ⦉
    ⦉⦉
⦉

§§ Notation ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ We denote the sum of two real numbers $x$ and $y$ by $x
    + y$. ⦉
⦉

§§ Properties ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ We can show the following.
