⦉

<statement type='proposition' text='Associative'>
  ‖ $x + (y + z) = (x + y) + z$ ⦉

  ‖ ⦉
</statement>
<statement type='proposition' text='Commutative'>
  ‖ $x + y = y + x$ ⦉
</statement>
<statement type='proposition' text='Identity'>
  ‖ The set of negative rational numbers is the additive
    identity. ⦉
</statement>
¶ ⦊
  ‖ We denote the additive identity of $𝗥$ under $+$ by $0_{𝗥}$. ⦉

  ‖ When it is clear from context, we call $0_{𝗥}$ “zero”. ⦉
